<TITLE> Govt mulls free medical service to autistic children </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  The government is mulling introducing pilot projects in five districts including Dhaka to offer free medical service to autistic chidren. "We are thinking of introducing free pilot service in five districts including Dhaka to ensure medical treatment for the autistic children," social welfare secretary Kamrunnesa Khanam told a workshop on 'The responsibilities of the mothers of autistic children" on Saturday. "If the pilot project runs successfully we will build such service centres in district and upazila levels," she said. The secretary outlined a number of government plans aimed at boosting facilities for the autistic and mentally disabled children. bdnew24.com social affairs editor Baby Moudud, who also spoke at the workshop, said: "The family, society and state will have to extend cooperation for the autistic children. The developed countries offer free treatment for these children." She asked all to come forward for the welfare of the autistic children and ensure their equal rights. In Bangladesh eight children in 1,000 are born with autism. bdne
